About
Originally built in 1869 as a lookout, this Rococo-style castle now houses the Henry Luce Nature Observatory and weather measuring devices.
Duration: 1-2 hours

    Enchantment
    Walking around Central Park I did not realise there was so much to see. I would definitely recommend spending at least half a day in the park as there are so many wonderful things to discover. One of these was the fairytale castle sat on a small bluff with a small lake below. It's a perfect picture opportunity! Belvedere Castle is open at certain times of the day and also for events. The architecture is truly beautiful and it is well worth checking out when you are in the park. Alternatively view it from afar and create your own stories about what goes on there.

Beautiful view indeed!
May 2024 • Couples
Belvedere means beautiful view in Italian and this place lived up to its name!

There are some narrow winding staircases to reach the top that could be difficult to navigate with mobility issues or if you are or found of tight spaces (which I am not but the staircases are not very long so I did not feel claustrophobic at any point).

This is definitely worth a stop on your exploration of Central Park.
